				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Lawyer for Melania Trump Threatens Defamation Suits Against News Outlets
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1860124">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							The Daily Mail is a UK paper and this kind of shit might work over there but good luck to a Hollywood attorney winning that case.  The American website is protected by American law because the legal standard for libel in journalism in the USA is that you can write pretty much anything about a public figure if it's either true or if it was published with no malice aforethought.  Proving malice in court is not that easy, and if this does wind up getting to a courtroom, the Defendants will be allowed to try to prove the truth of the matter and witnesses could be called that would describe the Plaintiff's past as a working whore.<br />
 <br />
Have these people never heard of the Streisand Effect?  Be careful, Pants-on-head Donald, or you'll spill the beans on your wife!
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
